    <title>Tuna Rice Bake</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    <part></part>


    <diet>FODMAP </diet>

    <ingredient>1 can creamed corn</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 cups cooked rice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/4 cup boiling water</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 teaspoon curry powder</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1-2 chicken stock cubes</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 bunch parsley chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 425 gms tuna in olive oil drained</ingredient>
    <ingredient>Grated tasty cheese </ingredient>
    <ingredient>Salt and Pepper to taste </ingredient>

    <step>
Put curry powder and stock cubes in boiling water and stir until dissolved. Place all ingredients in a baking dish except cheese and stir to combine then smooth top. Cover with grated cheese and place in preheated moderate (180D) oven for 20-30 minutes. Serve with salad if desired. Quick and super easy!
    </step>
</recipe>